National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: FIREBAUGH, CA
Accident Number: LAX84LA085
Date & Time: 12/01/1983, 0650 PST
Registration: N8837Q
Aircraft: AERO COMMANDER S2R
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries: 1 Minor
Flight Conducted Under: Part 137: Agricultural
 Analysis THE PLT REPORTED THAT HE FORGOT TO REMOVE THE AILERON BLOCKS BEFORE THE FLIGHT.
WHEN HE WAS TAKING OFF, THE ACFT BEGAN TO ROLL TO THE LEFT.
HE WAS UNABLE TO CONTROL THE BANK ATTITUDE WITH RUDDER CONTROL, SO HE 'CUT' THE POWER.
SECONDS LATER THE ACFT CRASH LANDED IN A SOFT, PLOWED FIELD & SUBSEQUENTLY CAME TO REST INVERTED.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: Findings Occurrence #1: LOSS OF CONTROL - IN FLIGHT Phase of Operation: TAKEOFF - INITIAL CLIMB Findings 1.
(C) FLT CONTROL SYST,AILERON CONTROL - LOCKED 2.
(C) AIRCRAFT PREFLIGHT - IMPROPER - PILOT IN COMMAND 3.
AIRCRAFT HANDLING - NOT POSSIBLE - PILOT IN COMMAND 4.
: 6000 lbs Time Since Last Inspection: 15 Hours Engines: 1 Reciprocating Airframe Total Time: 6317 Hours Engine Manufacturer: P&W ELT: Not installed Engine Model/Series: R-1340-AN-1 Registered Owner: TRI AIR INC.
